I was able to consume the AutoScaling service from an instance using an instance profile via the AWS CLI (after modifying the boto timeout used to detect when running in AWS):

{code}
root@i:~# aws --endpoint-url http://169.254.169.254:8773/services/AutoScaling/ autoscaling create-launch-configuration --image-id emi-52AF3722 --instance-type m1.small --launch-configuration-name Config1
root@i:~# aws --endpoint-url http://169.254.169.254:8773/services/AutoScaling/ autoscaling describe-launch-configurations
{
    "LaunchConfigurations": [
        {
            "LaunchConfigurationARN": "arn:aws:autoscaling::927772832466:launchConfiguration:7b750d91-8e76-4f33-8a97-1afab93a325a:launchConfigurationName/Config1", 
            "InstanceMonitoring": {
                "Enabled": true
            }, 
            "ImageId": "emi-52AF3722", 
            "LaunchConfigurationName": "Config1", 
            "CreatedTime": "2013-10-15T01:27:58.948Z", 
            "InstanceType": "m1.small"
        }
    ]
}
{code}

I don't see an assume role policy listed in this issue. You should ensure that EC2 instances are permitted to assume the role you are using in the instance profile.

[~sjones],

I see what you mean here.  So, I am curious, if I did the following:

* Changed the following property from port 8773 to port 80:
{code}
PROPERTY	bootstrap.webservices.port	8773
{code}
* Restart the CLC
* Attempt to run the test again, but use the following:
** In boto config:
{code}
ubuntu@euca-172-17-184-187:~$ cat .boto
[Boto]
autoscale_endpoint = autoscaling.euca-hspencer.eucalyptus-systems.com
{code}
** when setting the connection point in the ipython session:
{code}
In [4]: autoscale = boto.connect_autoscale(is_secure=False,path='/services/AutoScaling/',debug=2)
{code}
Would it get around this problem?

My thinking here is if we can use this as an option, that this would help with other tools who don't allow for custom port configuration (this has happened before as well, and had to figure out another alternative; see EUCA-5735 for an example).
